        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 1:54PM EDT by NWS Wilmington OH</headline>
        <description>At 154 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was located near Lewisburg,
moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph, pea size hail, and very heavy
rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Hail may cause minor damage to
vegetation. Visibility will be poor and hydroplaning is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Dayton, Huber Heights, Trotwood, Vandalia, Englewood, Tipp City, West
Milton, Lewisburg, Brown, Riverside, Clayton, Union, Brookville,
Shiloh, Phillipsburg, Eldorado, Verona, West Manchester, Potsdam, and
Gordon.

This includes the following Interstates...
I-70 in Ohio between mile markers 9 and 40.
I-75 in Ohio between mile markers 56 and 68.

If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a sturdy building.

Motorists should slow down and use extra caution.

To report hazardous weather conditions, go to our website at
weather.gov/iln and submit your report via social media, when you can
do so safely.
</description>
